This paper discusses boosting algorithms and their sensitivity to random label noise. The topic of boosting is primarily related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve datasets and performance evaluation, which are also relevant to data science (cs.DS) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses margin distributions, which are a concept commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
